The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Geneva, May 13: Former European Union trade chief Pascal Lamy is virtually certain of becoming the next head of the World Trade Organisation (WTO) after his only rival said on Friday he would pull out. Uruguayan diplomat Carlos Perez del Castillo, who was contesting the job of WTO director-general, said he would ask his government to withdraw his candidacy after he came second in a final round of polling among the WTO?s 148 member states. 

 Mumbai, May 13: The Sebi today said the broking subsidiaries of bourses and their registered sub-brokers will have to comply with regulations for brokers and sub-brokers from June 1.

 Mumbai, May 13: The Reserve Bank has raised the ceiling on Indian companies? overseas investments in joint ventures and wholly-owned subsidiaries to 200 per cent of the net worth from 100 per cent.

 New Delhi, May 13: The government is planning a national drug authority, which will closely monitor the quality of drugs, said Union health minister Anbumani Ramadoss.

 New Delhi, May 13: Parliament today passed a bill to set up and regulate credit information companies.




